**CASTING CALL ‚Äî Multigenerational Family - Freelance Preferred **

We‚Äôre looking for a warm, authentic **multigenerational family** (grandparents, parents, and children) to appear in an upcoming **product branding photo/video shoot **for Balance of Nature. We‚Äôre seeking real families or talent groups who naturally represent connection, joy, and everyday moments together.

**Who we‚Äôre looking for:**
* Families representing 2‚Äì3 generations
   * Female & Male Talent Ages 50+ 
   * Female & Male Talent Ages 30+ 
   * Children ages 5+
* All ethnicities encouraged to apply
* Comfortable on camera and able to interact naturally together
* Families together are welcome to apply, but if it‚Äôs just you individually please apply as well because we might be able to cast you together with others. 

**Shoot details:**
* Location: St. George, UT
* Date(s): End of February
* Compensation: $65-$85/hr depending on experience. We can also do daily rates for full families, if hired. 
* Usage: Brand marketing and advertising materials. **Freelance preferred.** 

**To submit:**
Please send recent family photos, names/ages of participants, location, and contact information to [abustillo@bonadmin.com](mailto:abustillo@bonadmin.com) with the subject line **‚ÄúMultigenerational Family Casting.‚Äù**

We can‚Äôt wait to meet your family!

items.text:
FINAL CASTING CALL!
COMIC CON DOCUMENTARY | CASTING CALL 

Hello,

I am currently on my BA Hons Degree in Media Production at South Gloucestershire and Stroud College. 

I am doing a 6 - minute documentary that uses a core participants to explore how Cosplay is not a performance but entertainment, a way identity is expressed, shaped and performed.

It will document the participants' experience and highlight the experience from a first - time attendees, offering both a personal insight and broader perspective of UK Comic Con Culture. 

I need someone to Cosplay Catwoman aged 18 - 40 at Bristol Comic Con on the 8th March 2026 at Ashton Gate Stadium. 

There will also be an interview segment following the event.

Please let me know if you'd be interested?

I will pay for your ticket too, it's from 10:30am - 16:00pm

I'd pay you ¬£200.00

It's for my BA Hons Degree FMP and determines if I pass or fail.

message.text:
Save the date: 30 March 2026.

Actors don‚Äôt need another generic ‚Äúask ChatGPT‚Äù shortcut. We need clarity under pressure. No time left, the self-tape‚Äôs due and you‚Äôre still second-guessing every beat?

The Actors Copilot is human-led, AI-assisted: AI helps you organise, highlight and break things down‚Ä¶ so you can focus on the work that actually matters.

And it goes far beyond tools. Inside the platform we will have interactive zoom sessions that go  deeply into what it is to be an actor: craft, mindset, industry realities, and the inner work‚Äîhow to mine your past, sharpen your instincts, and make braver, truer choices on tape and on set.

30 March 2026. Follow for the build-up.

#TheActorsCopilot #Actors #ActorLife #WorkingActor #SelfTape SelfTapeAuditions CharacterWork ActingCoach ActingTraining AuditionPrep AIForActors FilmTV Casting ActorCommunity

Szukamy kogo≈õ **z Gliwic lub okolic: Zabrze, Katowice** najdalej. Postaƒá ta bƒôdzie nosiƒá mundur polski podporucznika.Same zdjƒôcia bƒôdƒÖ realizowane na terenie Gliwic. Niestety nie zwracamy koszt√≥w podr√≥≈ºy. Postaƒá mƒô≈ºczyzny pojawi siƒô w pierwszym odcinku i zostanie zabita przez odzia≈Ç niemiecki. Pojawi siƒô te≈º w retrospekcji bitwy w 1919 roku z Bolszewikami gdzie zostanie ranny w nogƒô. Oczywi≈õcie mile widziane do≈õwiadczenie pracy z tekstem. Bƒôdziemy realizowaƒá mini serial oparty o wƒÖtki grupy okultystycznej ‚Äô‚Äô**Ahnenerbe‚Äô**‚Äô kt√≥ra chce zdobyƒá s≈Çynne artefakty ale w tym kto≈õ im chce przeszkadzaƒá. Projekt bƒôdzie  siƒô sk≈Çadaƒá z 6 odcink√≥w po 10/12 minut ka≈ºdy. Bƒôdziemy te≈º sukcesywnie dodawaƒá inne og≈Çoszenia zwiƒÖzane z tym projektem. Mile widziane zdjƒôcia aktualne. Na zdjƒôciu powy≈ºej osoba bƒôdzie mieƒá podobny kostium.** **Umieszczone materia≈Çy sƒÖ z naszej sesji.** Nie bƒôdzie to zlecenie p≈Çatne.**

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCE8KyfwpyFGzzwUDqdwy74g

Wiƒôcej informacji na Priv

W produkcji znajdƒÖ siƒô osoby, kt√≥re bƒôdƒÖ chcieƒá walczyƒá i potƒôpiaƒá te wielkie z≈Ço jakim by≈Ç nazizm. items.text:
**Deepen Your Truth, Presence & Craft ‚Äì Meisner Workshop in Helsinki** üåü
**February 18-19   I   with Nita Arpiainen**

Do you ever feel like your acting is better when you‚Äôre performing alone? Free, relaxed, and without anyone watching, yet struggling to access that same truth on set, in auditions, or in front of the camera.

Many actors experience this: moments of effortless expression alone, yet pressure from cameras, lines, and instructions seem to block the same authenticity in real settings. The challenge isn‚Äôt your talent. It‚Äôs learning to **bring that truthful acting in front of an audience with more ease and confidence**.

That‚Äôs what **Authentic Me**, our two-evening Meisner Technique workshop is designed to do. Through exercises that build presence, impulse, and truthful connection, you‚Äôll learn to **access your authentic acting anywhere ‚Äî on stage, on set, and in auditions**.

**You‚Äôll learn how to:**
‚ú® Respond truthfully without planning or performing
‚ú® Access your authentic emotional impulses
‚ú® Listen to & build deeper connection with your scene partners
‚ú® Release tension and overthinking
‚ú® Trust your instincts and impulses
‚ú® React naturally, creating honest & compelling behavior

And this all within a very safe space and a supportive group.

Open to actors, directors, writers, creatives, and anyone who wants to live and relate more authentically. No previous experience needed! 

**Limited spots ‚Äì Reserve your spot now:**
[https://www.actorsacademy.fi/authentic-me

](https://www.actorsacademy.fi/authentic-me)*‚ÄúAn exceptionally guided introduction to the Meisner technique. Nita‚Äôs deep understanding of the work creates a safe, precise and playful space where authentic acting emerges naturally. Powerful not only for your craft, but for how you listen, respond and live.‚Äù*

**Feb 18‚Äì19, 2026 (Wed & Thu)**
**16:00‚Äì21:00**
**Actors Academy Studio, Helsinki**

Watch our video on the fear we often feel of not belonging or not being accepted: [https://www.instagram.com/p/DUTJctuDbyF/

](https://www.instagram.com/p/DUTJctuDbyF/)üå± Step into your **truth, presence, and creative power**.

Def-G Productions is looking for extras for filming of an upcoming Christmas film on Saturday, February 28th and Sunday, March 1st

Location for Saturday will be in Burlington, NC area and requires 20-30 people. All ages welcome (sorry no babies on set or young children that cannot sit still or quiet during filming). 

Dress code: funeral attire/business casual during winter.

Location on Sunday will be in Greensboro, NC. 20-30 adults 18+ in age for a night club scene. 

Dress code: Festive, holiday wear.

All serious inquires and for more details; please comment on this post or reach out to Def-G Productions directly at Defgpros@gmail.com

Bundesweit, m.w.d.

Filmschaffende gesucht.
Alter spielt keine Rolle und Du jast alle Freiheiten, eine sympathischen, erfolgreichen Initiative mit Deiner Hilfe mitzugestalten oder zu leiten.

Faire Gagen ist zur Marke gewachsen.

Gerne Nachricht via PN an Faire Gagen oder an

EVC Talent Casting Show 2026 ‚Äì Jetzt bewerben und Teil einer au√üergew√∂hnlichen Show werden

Die EVC Talent Casting Show startet 2026 in eine neue, spannende Staffel und bietet K√ºnstlerinnen und K√ºnstlern erneut eine B√ºhne, um sich einem breiten Publikum zu pr√§sentieren. Der Auftakt der neuen Staffel ist f√ºr das Fr√ºhjahr 2026 geplant. Bewerbungen sind ab sofort m√∂glich.

Gesucht werden Talente aus allen k√ºnstlerischen Bereichen: Musikerinnen und Musiker, Bands, T√§nzerinnen und T√§nzer (Solo, Duo oder Gruppe), Artistinnen und Artisten, Comedians sowie Menschen mit au√üergew√∂hnlichen oder besonderen F√§higkeiten. Ganz gleich, ob Sie bereits B√ºhnenerfahrung haben, als etablierte K√ºnstlerin oder etablierter K√ºnstler t√§tig sind, nach einer kreativen Pause wieder durchstarten m√∂chten oder Ihr Talent zum ersten Mal vor Publikum zeigen entscheidend ist Ihre Leidenschaft und Begeisterung f√ºr das, was Sie tun.

Die EVC Talent Casting Show versteht sich als Plattform zur F√∂rderung von Nachwuchstalenten ebenso wie zur Unterst√ºtzung etablierter K√ºnstlerinnen und K√ºnstler und kreativer Pers√∂nlichkeiten, die neue Impulse suchen. Teilnehmen k√∂nnen Kinder, Jugendliche und Erwachsene ab 6 Jahren. Minderj√§hrige ben√∂tigen die Begleitung eines Erwachsenen.

Wenn Sie Ihr Talent pr√§sentieren und unsere Jury √ºberzeugen m√∂chten, bewerben Sie sich jetzt online unter:
https://electricvisionscleve.de/casting.html

Wir freuen uns auf zahlreiche Bewerbungen und darauf, viele beeindruckende Talente kennenzulernen.

topComments.text:
Im more than just the admin. I am unleashing my passion for the arts from rocking the stage to standing in the spotlight, on and off stage, ive had a taste of it all. I've had the privilege of being part of some incredible entertainment experiences. From captivating performances to caring for others, Multi-talented mama on a mission! Actress starring in the YouTube series "The Missi and Kali Show: Noelle and Holly's Christmas Blackout", captivating voice artist lending my voice to the beloved character Carly Standfields in Minecraft Time Agent, the YouTube series I have been making waves in the world of entertainment since 2020 well actually since 2013 when I landed my first project started working toward my goal in 2011. I bring stories to life. and model bringing characters to life  not just on screen and but in print. With features in prestigious publications like Woodbangers Magazine, Celebrity Magazine, My Little Matilda, and The Trendy Icon, I have graced runways for Fairytale Fashions' enchanting prom dress collection back in 2013. Former vocalist with Woodbangers turned background extra and stand-in for awesome productions like "Green Room," "The Librarians," and even made it in a Seattle Super Bowl XLIX commercial!

To fueling my talent with knowledge, I honed my acting skills under the guidance of renowned coach Doug Larson in 2014 while continuing to expand my craft with Allison's acting lessons in 2023 and to continuing acting lessons in 2023 with Timeless Dream Studios. Follow along on this extraordinary journey as I bring characters to life and inspire others through the magic of storytelling. With a background in healthcare nurture the  well-being of others and mixology  creating unforgettable concoctions behind the bar. 

I have a  EFSET certificate in English, and skills in video production, voice acting, photography, modeling, and singing. I am always eager to learn new things, challenge myself, and expand my horizons. I am looking to build my network, meet new people, and work on exciting and meaningful projects. I'm ready to embark on new adventures and bring characters to life.

üé¨ DENVER / AURORA FILMMAKERS ‚Äî VOLUNTEER CREW CALL (IMDb CREDIT) üé¨
I‚Äôm filming a documentary in Lyons, CO on Monday, February 9, and I‚Äôm looking for a small volunteer crew‚Äîespecially a Director of Photography‚Äîto help capture an important story.

This film has been built entirely by volunteers‚Äîpeople who believe stories can actually change systems. We‚Äôre keeping the crew small, intentional, and respectful of everyone‚Äôs time.

### üé• Roles Needed:

‚Ä¢ Director of Photography (priority)  

‚Ä¢ Assistant Camera (AC)  

‚Ä¢ Lighting / Gaffer  

‚Ä¢ Production Assistant (PA)

### üìç Shoot Details:

üìÖ Monday, Feb 9  

üìç Anschutz Medical Campus ‚Äì Aurora, CO  

üéû Documentary (mental health, prevention, community)  

üé¨ IMDb credit provided  

‚è± Short, focused shoot day

This project centers on mental health prevention, belonging, and real human stories‚Äînot spectacle, not fluff. If you‚Äôre a DP or crew member who cares about purpose-driven filmmaking, meaningful collaboration, and telling stories that actually matter, I‚Äôd love to connect.

Please comment or DM with:

‚Ä¢ The role you‚Äôre interested in  

‚Ä¢ A link to your work, reel, or IG (if you have one)

Even sharing this with someone in your network helps more than you know.  

Thank you üíô

items.text:
Title: Saturdays

Genre: Thriller/Comedy

Logline: After accidentally taking a new designer drug on the way to a Halloween party, three broke nobodies become viral vigilantes in a city on the edge but their rise to infamy puts them in the cross-hairs of a charismatic cartel leader.

Role:

Dave (30-50) Unkillable, unshakable, and possibly unmedicated. Somehow still endearing. Dave is an uber driver, a hype man, and a secret weapon and comes from a different era. He‚Äôs the uncle at thanksgiving that you hope didn‚Äôt bring a bottle of scotch (you know he did). A chaotic wildcard who might be a genius... or just very, very lucky.

Production Type: Indie

Production Company: Loste Films

Contact Information: [luke@lostefilms.com](mailto:luke@lostefilms.com)

Run Time: Feature

Compensation: Catering/Crafty provided during proof of concept shoot. Compensation for future shoot dates is open to negotiation.

Audition Information: Send an email with headshot, resume and reel. The first round of auditions will be self-tape, then we will have in-person callbacks (downtown Denver area).

Shooting Schedule: Late February. Other shoot dates TBD

Filming Location: Highlands Ranch and Denver area

Project Description: Saturdays is an upcoming feature film we‚Äôre currently shooting the beginning of to use as a proof of concept. The scenes in the proof of concept are still being used in the final movie, which will be shot later on in the year. Due to scheduling conflicts we had to recast this role and are looking for someone who can carry mystery, comedy, and spiritual invincibility. There‚Äôs also lots of room for improv in the role. Some character inspirations include Erlich Eachman (Silicon Valley), Frank Reynolds (It‚Äôs Always Sunny), Red (Pineapple Express), Jay (Clerks), The Dude (The Big Lebowski). Attached pictures are the location/vehicles we have locked in for the first scene you‚Äôll be shooting with us.

IMDB Link: [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39423188/](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39423188/)

üì£üé¨** CASTING CALL ‚Äì SHORT MOCKUMENTARY FILM**

We are casting lead and supporting speaking roles for RAPID, a 10-minute mockumentary graduation film produced as part of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

The film will be shot in Bristol from 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026.
This is a student project, unpaid with travel expenses and food provided, intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

**STORY:**

RAPID follows a small documentary crew as they capture former sprint star Ian Hitchworth‚Äôs attempted comeback through a chaotic charity race. Told in a deadpan mockumentary style, the film blends awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability, allowing humour to emerge through character, timing, and uncomfortable silences.

**ROLES:**

**INTERVIEWER**

Male, 20s‚Äì40s
Dry but playful documentary interviewer. Strong comic timing, curiosity, and the ability to let humour land through reactions and pauses.
Reference: Marty DiBergi (*This Is Spinal Tap*)

**CHARITY INTERVIEWER**

Any gender, 20s‚Äì40s
On-screen presenter at a charity athletics event. Confident, warm, and camera-friendly.

**DAISY**

Female, 20s
Competitive sprinter and charity race winner. Athletic, sincere and grounded.

**TIA**

Female, 20s
Sports shop manager and Ian‚Äôs boss. Stern, reasonable, and just trying to do her job. Strong comedic timing, with humour landing through micro-expressions and acknowledgment of the camera.
Reference: Jennifer Taylor Clarke (*The Office UK*)

**KEY INFO:**

Location: Bristol

Shoot dates: 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026

Payment: Voluntary (travel expenses & food provided)

**TO APPLY:**

Please send a **headshot** and **CV** (or Spotlight / Mandy link) to: **[rapidfilm2026@gmail.com](mailto:rapidfilm2026@gmail.com)**

Told in a deadpan mockumentary style, the film blends awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability, allowing humour to emerge through character, timing, and uncomfortable silences.

**ROLES:**

**INTERVIEWER**

Male, 20s‚Äì40s
Dry but playful documentary interviewer. Strong comic timing, curiosity, and the ability to let humour land through reactions and pauses.
Reference: Marty DiBergi (*This Is Spinal Tap*)

**CHARITY INTERVIEWER**

Any gender, 20s‚Äì40s
On-screen presenter at a charity athletics event. Confident, warm, and camera-friendly.

**DAISY**

Female, 20s
Competitive sprinter and charity race winner. Athletic, sincere and grounded.

**TIA**

Female, 20s
Sports shop manager and Ian‚Äôs boss. Stern, reasonable, and just trying to do her job. Strong comedic timing, with humour landing through micro-expressions and acknowledgment of the camera.
Reference: Jennifer Taylor Clarke (*The Office UK*)

**KEY INFO:**

Location: Bristol

Shoot dates: 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026

Payment: Voluntary (travel expenses & food provided)

**TO APPLY:**

Please send a **headshot** and **CV** (or Spotlight / Mandy link) to: **[rapidfilm2026@gmail.com](mailto:rapidfilm2026@gmail.com)**

**Can you spot the fake Moms? üïµÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüçº**

We filmed a social experiment right here in Vancouver to see if intuition is real. We put 6 Moms and 2 Imposters in a room. If the Moms vote out the fakes, they split the cash. If the Imposters survive, they steal it all.

We just dropped the full episode on YouTube, but here is a sneak peek of the chaos.

Watch the full episode: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v1XlutsymMk&t](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v1XlutsymMk&t)

-- CASTING CALL --

YORK ACTORS WANTED!

The casting for our final year student film, Murder in C Minor, is open! 

Our film is a musical journey that fuses the spectacle of Hollywood‚Äôs Golden Age with the suspense of a noir thriller. Featuring three original songs, Murder in C Minor is a tale of fame, performance, and deception. 

We are looking for enthusiastic actors local to the York area to help us bring Murder in C Minor to life! The opportunity is unpaid, but travel expenses will be covered, and catering will be provided! 

All details on characters and the project are in the photos below and on our audition pack.

If you have any questions at all, please get in touch with us at murderincminor@gmail.com

We are also happy to conduct in-person auditions for anyone who may prefer. Please email us for more information. 

If you want to find out more, check out the audition pack in our link tree: https://linktr.ee/murderinCminor

items.text:
Casting call - Unpaid.
Looking for two adults to act in a short film in Gloucester, England.

Roles: Prisoner, HM Transport officer.

Age: 30-50

Gender: Male 

Language: English

Rehearsal: Saturday 7th March (2026)

Filming date: Sunday 8th March (2026)

Hours: 10am - 5pm (1 hour lunch)

Location - Alney island (near Dunelm)

No experience needed as this will be a learning together on the days as this will be my first production, directing ect also.

Candidates must be able bodied and be ok to be in close contact.

If interested please drop an email to

davesventurestudios@gmail.com - title Jail Break and tell me something about you and experience, plus which role you would like.

Those are selected, we will need to meet up two weeks prior to filming to run through the script and the overall plan of the short film.

For more details on this short film have been/will be posting updates on the page here on Facebook as production and filming progress.

Upon this one is successful a prequel and sequel will be put into production.

If you know anyone who would be interested please tag or message them.

Thank you for your time.

items.text:
1 / 4
True Measures!

Character Breakdown

Lead
DEMS TASSY, 22, a Haitian national, stands tall, brawny, with a happy, healthy and beautiful dark skin. Fluent in English and Haitian-Creole. Intermediate in French.

Supporting
MONA LEROUGE, 40‚Äôs, Dems‚Äô aunt is a beautiful woman with a nice figure and always has a conservative look. (Caramel complexion) Fluent in English, French and Haitian-Creole.

SABINE TASSY, 19, Dems‚Äô little sister, is a trendy and free spirit female. (Fair skinned). Fluent in English and Haitian-Creole.

ANITA TASSY, Dems‚Äô mother, late 50‚Äôs is diabetic. Fair skinned. She has good fashion sense. She speaks Haitian-Creole and French only.

SERGE TASSY, Dems‚Äô father, 60‚Äôs, is a tall, dark skinned man - very fashionable and slick. A former high ranking officer in the Haitian army. He speaks French and Haitian-Creole only. No gut.

SIMONE CHARLES, early 50‚Äôs, is Serge‚Äôs mistress. Thick woman. She is fluent in English, French and Haitian-Creole.

Olivia, late 20‚Äôs, is a natural beauty, husky, brazen, articulate, orderly, and a prompt racing thoroughbred who needs help with her appearance - you‚Äôd think she shops at thrift stores. She speaks Haitian-Creole fluently.

TREASURER GROVENSKY, 20‚Äôs, is a smart, ambitious, reticent and frugal nerd. Although he is slow in manner, he is always on top of the agenda.

MEDGYN ‚ÄúSTALLION‚Äù PENARD, late 20‚Äôs, is a thorough, sassy Haitian beauty, complemented with both style and grace. She‚Äôs the perfect mix of elegance and raunch. She speaks Haitian-Creole fluently.

JAMES MCCARVER, 50‚Äôs, is tall and fit. He wears a handlebar mustache. He teaches statistics. (Caucasian).

FLOR COOPER, Dems‚Äô girlfriend, is a sublime beauty. Growing up Guyanese gives her a unique spice. She is in her 20‚Äôs. Light ebony complexion.

YVONNE PADMORE (60‚Äôs), Flor‚Äôs aunt, sews with a machine. A very dark woman. She wears thick prescription glasses.  

2 / 4
Supporting
 
ANTOINE BORGELLA is a middle aged Haitian man. An avid smoker and a lottery fanatic. He has a habit of moving his jaw side to side. A wise guy. He speaks English, French and Haitian-Creole fluently.

MARIE-CARMELLE BORGELLA, 50‚Äôs, is a well-endowed, olive toned, long hair woman. A very sophisticated woman. She speaks English, French and Haitian-Creole fluently.

ALBERT MARKOWITZ, 60‚Äôs, is a Criminal Defense and immigration Lawyer. Scammer. Caucasian.

PATRICK BORGELLA, 25, lives on the edge - a vagrant at best. He‚Äôs street smart and, of course, a ladies man. Indulging in alcoholism and heavy drug use are his coping mechanisms.  

PRESIDENT TRUMP, 70‚Äôs, holds nothing back. Caucasian.

MICHAEL, 20‚Äôs, is well-built and charismatic. (Simone‚Äôs son).

MAMBO also known as a Vodou Priestess. She is in her 50‚Äôs. She speaks English and Haitian-Creole well.

ELIGIBLE BACHELOR is a tall, handsome and pretentious black man with slick hair. He is between 48 and 55 years old.

LIONEL, Mona‚Äôs husband, is a womanizer. He is in his 50‚Äôs. He dresses to impress. He speaks English and Haitian-Creole.

HUSTLER, mid-aged, is a very charismatic and slick, foundationally black, American man. He sells cologne and perfume.

JEAN-EDDY, Dems‚Äô childhood friend, is a featherweight who stands 5‚Äô7‚Äù tall. He is a menace. He is tatted with a barcode on his neck, very slick and witty. He speaks English and Haitian-Creole.

KITCHEN WORKER, 40‚Äôs, has a raspy voice.

JEAN BASTIEN, late 40‚Äôs, is a dark, tall, and renowned Haitian scholar, columnist, community leader and activist with a very warm personality. He speaks Haitian-Creole as well.

WHITE MALE dressed in white linen attire with a straw hat. He is bald headed. He is in his late 50‚Äôs.

CLIFF is a black security guard. He is between 47-55 years old.

RICHARD BACCHUS, late 50‚Äôs, is a News Reporter. Caucasian.
3 / 4
Supporting

ISABEL SOTO is a 45-year-old dignified Latina woman with good fashion sense. She is Salsa and Merengue in one.

DENISE KNOWLES, 55, is a fair skinned, Afro-centric woman. She is the Research & Development Coordinator at Janssen, Pharmaceutical Companies of Johnson & Johnson.

TAH is an African-American gambler. He is in his late 20‚Äôs.

CASEY MALLOY is J&J CEO. He is white, tall, fit and charismatic. He is in his 50‚Äôs.

An ELDERLY WHITE MALE with disheveled sports attire listens to the evening news on a portable radio on. He is in his 50‚Äôs.  

Casting Calls!

When:
Saturday, February 7th, 2026 from 4:00PM to 7:00PM
Saturday, February 14th, 2026 from 10:00AM to 1:00PM

Location: 520 Eighth Ave. 3rd Fl.  New York, NY 10018

Please send headshots, reels and resume to Tm.casting26@gmail.com.

üî• NOW CASTING: THE CULT: LIVE üî•
A chilling, edge-of-your-seat supernatural thriller made for the digital age.

THE STORY (READ THIS üëÄ):
Skylar is a famous teenage vlogger living the dream, millions of followers, nonstop views, perfect life. But when she moves from sunny California into a dark Victorian home in Mount Clemens, MI, everything changes.

One night, Skylar ends her livestream‚Ä¶
‚ö†Ô∏è Seconds later, it turns back on by itself.
What unfolds next exposes the house‚Äôs paranormal past LIVE to millions around the world.

As the night spirals into terror, Skylar becomes the target of a powerful high priestess from an ancient demonic cult.
Faith, disbelief, technology, and social media collide as good vs. evil plays out in real time with the internet watching.

This isn‚Äôt just horror.
This is spiritual warfare in the age of livestreams.

Stage West Playhouse along with director Mathew Root and assistant director Jacob Mandelin are thrilled to announce auditions for "The Glass Menagerie".

IMPORTANT DATES:
Audition Dates: February 6 at 7 PM and February 8 at 1 PM, at the playhouse
Show Dates: April 24-26

AUDITION REQUIREMENTS:
Auditions will consist of cold readings. Video auditions will be accepted until 1 PM on February 8. Video auditions must include your name, address, phone number and email, as well as if you are auditioning for a specific role. Please include any conflicts you have between audition dates and show dates. Video auditions can be emailed to mattroot1274@gmail.com.

SYNOPSIS:
Tennessee Williams‚Äô The Glass Menagerie is a poignant memory play about family, dreams, and the painful tension between illusion and reality.

Set in a small St. Louis apartment during the 1930s, the story is narrated by Tom Wingfield, who looks back on his youth living with his domineering mother Amanda and his fragile, painfully shy sister Laura. Amanda, abandoned years earlier by her husband, clings to memories of her Southern belle past and is determined to secure a future for Laura, whose physical disability and extreme anxiety keep her isolated from the world.

Amanda pressures Tom, who longs to escape his monotonous warehouse job and pursue a life of adventure and writing, to bring home a ‚Äúgentleman caller‚Äù for Laura. When Tom finally invites his coworker Jim O‚ÄôConnor to dinner, the evening unfolds with hope, awkwardness, and heartbreak‚Äîforcing each character to confront their illusions and the limits of their dreams.

ROLES AVAILABLE:
Tom Wingfield (Male, 20s‚Äì30s)
Narrator / Son
A restless young man trapped between responsibility and desire for freedom. Tom works in a warehouse to support his family but dreams of becoming a poet and adventurer. He narrates the story from the future, reflecting on the guilt and longing he still carries after leaving his family behind.

Amanda Wingfield (Female, late 40s‚Äì60s)  Mother
A faded Southern belle clinging desperately to memories of her youth and the illusion of gentility. Amanda is controlling, talkative, and fiercely determined to secure a future for her children, especially Laura. Beneath her humor and bluster lies deep fear of abandonment and poverty.

Laura Wingfield (Female, late teens‚Äì20s)  Daughter
Extremely shy and emotionally fragile, Laura has a slight physical disability and crippling social anxiety. She escapes into her collection of delicate glass animals and old records. Gentle, kind, and painfully self-conscious, she embodies vulnerability and quiet hope.

Jim O‚ÄôConnor (Male, 20s‚Äì30s)
The Gentleman Caller
Tom‚Äôs coworker and Amanda‚Äôs long-awaited ‚Äúgentleman caller.‚Äù Once a popular high-school hero, Jim is now an ordinary young man with big dreams and relentless optimism. Kind and well-meaning, though sometimes unaware of the emotional impact he has on others.

Questions? Contact the director at mattroot1274@gmail.com.

üì£üé¨** CASTING CALL ‚Äì SHORT MOCKUMENTARY FILM**

We are casting lead and supporting speaking roles for RAPID, a 10-minute mockumentary graduation film produced as part of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

The film will be shot in Bristol from 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026.
This is a student project, unpaid with travel expenses and food provided, intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

**STORY:**

RAPID follows a small documentary crew as they capture former sprint star Ian Hitchworth‚Äôs attempted comeback through a chaotic charity race. Told in a deadpan mockumentary style, the film blends awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability, allowing humour to emerge through character, timing, and uncomfortable silences.

**ROLES:**

**INTERVIEWER**

Male, 20s‚Äì40s
Dry but playful documentary interviewer. Strong comic timing, curiosity, and the ability to let humour land through reactions and pauses.
Reference: Marty DiBergi (*This Is Spinal Tap*)

**CHARITY INTERVIEWER**

Any gender, 20s‚Äì40s
On-screen presenter at a charity athletics event. Confident, warm, and camera-friendly.

**DAISY**

Female, 20s
Competitive sprinter and charity race winner. Athletic, sincere and grounded.

**TIA**

Female, 20s
Sports shop manager and Ian‚Äôs boss. Stern, reasonable, and just trying to do her job. Strong comedic timing, with humour landing through micro-expressions and acknowledgment of the camera.
Reference: Jennifer Taylor Clarke (*The Office UK*)

**KEY INFO:**

Location: Bristol

Shoot dates: 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026

Payment: Voluntary (travel expenses & food provided)

**TO APPLY:**

Please send a **headshot** and **CV** (or Spotlight / Mandy link) to: **[rapidfilm2026@gmail.com](mailto:rapidfilm2026@gmail.com)**

üì£üé¨** CASTING CALL ‚Äì SHORT MOCKUMENTARY FILM**

We are casting lead and supporting speaking roles for RAPID, a 10-minute mockumentary graduation film produced as part of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

The film will be shot in Bristol from 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026.
This is a student project, unpaid with travel expenses and food provided, intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

**STORY:**

RAPID follows a small documentary crew as they capture former sprint star Ian Hitchworth‚Äôs attempted comeback through a chaotic charity race. Told in a deadpan mockumentary style, the film blends awkward comedy with moments of vulnerability, allowing humour to emerge through character, timing, and uncomfortable silences.

**ROLES:**

**INTERVIEWER**

Male, 20s‚Äì40s
Dry but playful documentary interviewer. Strong comic timing, curiosity, and the ability to let humour land through reactions and pauses.
Reference: Marty DiBergi (*This Is Spinal Tap*)

**CHARITY INTERVIEWER**

Any gender, 20s‚Äì40s
On-screen presenter at a charity athletics event. Confident, warm, and camera-friendly.

**DAISY**

Female, 20s
Competitive sprinter and charity race winner. Athletic, sincere and grounded.

**TIA**

Female, 20s
Sports shop manager and Ian‚Äôs boss. Stern, reasonable, and just trying to do her job. Strong comedic timing, with humour landing through micro-expressions and acknowledgment of the camera.
Reference: Jennifer Taylor Clarke (*The Office UK*)

**KEY INFO:**

Location: Bristol

Shoot dates: 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026

Payment: Voluntary (travel expenses & food provided)

**TO APPLY:**

Please send a **headshot** and **CV** (or Spotlight / Mandy link) to: **[rapidfilm2026@gmail.com](mailto:rapidfilm2026@gmail.com)**

items.text: Hey everyone! If you ever find yourself needing a reader for an audition, or you'd like to earn some extra cash being a reader for another actor, then head over to We Audition where you can do just that! It's an excellent source to help actors not only help other actors, but also to gain experience in script reading as well as coaching and getting coached! It's a genuinely cool experience that helps you learn the ropes, especially if you are a beginner or have been in and out of the industry! Link below and you can use my code JASMINA25 to get 25% off when you sign up! I hope to see you all there!

I had the chance to share insights from my journey of standing up against the hostile infiltrations in our world while also promoting my upcoming short film premiere, 'Where are the Children?' 

The full interview is in the editing stage right now, but I wanted to share this snippet in the meantime!

**STUDENT SHORT FILM CASTING CALL **

Hi! I am looking for actors (NU) to be in my capstone student short film The Catfish in the CT/NY area. Shooting will be in Fairfield County, CT during the first two weekends of March. No/limited pay, depending on leftover budget. Travel and meals provided (CT/NY only). Familiarity or experience in comedy preferred. 

LOOKING FOR: 
* Two males in their 20s or late teens to play two college-aged characters. 
* One female in her 20s to play a college-aged character. 

Character Descriptions: 
* Gabe: Awkward, somewhat off-putting, non-muscular build 
* Damian: Pompous, average-slightly above average build and looks 
* Sara Lynn: Outgoing, confident, any build/look 

If you are interested, please email me with your headshot, resume, and/or reel at **david.r.goodman@outlook.com** . Thank you!

items.text:
**VOLUNTEER** Student Film Casting Call - Food Provided

Capilano University SMPA is searching for actors for our short film "The Show Must Go On."

Union and non union actors please submit! 

Casting Workbook submission link:
https://castingworkbook.com/open-breakdown.asp?bd=0170399

Alternatively, please DM me on Messenger or send an email to vedamaharaj@my.capilanou.ca. Please include your agency name if currently represented.

Shooting Mar 7th to Mar 9th.

Super senior Rhett Hanson is cruising through his second attempt at senior year when he's abruptly dragged into the lead role in the drama club's production. Faced with one final opportunity to succeed, he must battle with a resentful director and a formidable principal to not make a fool of himself - his graduation, and future, depend on it.

Lead Role

HANSON - Male 17 - 25 yrs.

Open ethnicity. An off-the-cuff renegade who's never believed he could succeed, and never felt the need to try. When faced with a decision to either succeed, or embarrass himself, Hanson needs to overcome his own self doubt and truly believe he can be good at something.

Supporting Lead Role

MAX - Male 17 - 19 yrs.

Open ethnicity. A snooty and egotistical freshman who directs the school's drama productions, hoping to gain popularity to rival Hanson's. Cripplingly insecure, he thrives in positions of power where everyone knows he's the head honcho.

Supporting Lead Role

PRINCIPAL BURNS - Male 40 - 55 yrs.

Open ethnicity. A cruel and intimidating traditionalist, Burns is a firm believer in the academics as the only path to success. Disgusted by Hanson's apathy, he's determined to see Hanson face the consequences of his inadequacy.

Supporting Role

BRIAN - Male 17 - 19 yrs.

Open ethnicity. A laid-back freshman burdened with the newfound anxiety of a stage manager. More disorganized than he should be, but managing to stay on top of things enough to keep the show running.

Featured Role

ACTOR - Any gender 17 - 19 yrs.

Open ethnicity. An overzealous theatre geek who dramatically over-commits to their role. 

Featured Role

FRESHMAN - Any gender 17 - 19 yrs.

Open ethnicity. A chronically stressed theatre enthusiast who takes on more responsibility than they should.

Voice-Over / Voice-Only Role

MC - Any gender 30 - 39 yrs.

Open ethnicity. A booming dramatic voice. Enough enthusiasm to make watching paint dry interesting.

Please let me know if you have any questions!

items.text:
CASTING CALL - SHORT FILM - UNPAID

No Prior Experience Required

Genre: Realist Drama

Location: Liverpool

Shoot dates: Saturday 20th June & Sunday 21st June

Sunday Roast is about how a family that has been dysfunctional for years reacts to the introduction of an outsider. Actor-led and dialogue driven, this is a film about the uncomfortable moments that we all put up with in order to get by in life.

If you‚Äôre interested in any of the below roles please contact me at [sundayroastshort@gmail.com](mailto:sundayroastshort@gmail.com). Please send headshots and showreels if you have them.

SHARON (40s)
Sharon is a woman who has learned to survive by keeping everything in motion. She believes it is her responsibility as a mother to look after her family, even when it costs her personally. At her core she wants only her family‚Äôs happiness.
Her relationship with her mother is the central wound of her adult life. She knows exactly where it hurts, but she also knows that naming it only deepens the pain. So she gets on with life, convinced this is the only way to get by

NAN (60s-70s)
Nan is socially adept, affectionate, and completely blind to the harm she causes. She is the family matriarch and commands unquestioned respect, even in her most irrational moments. She does not see herself as cruel; in her mind, she is honest, wise, and entitled to her views.
Her power is quiet and absolute. She never raises her voice or argues. The family has been circling her moods for decades.

LAUREN (mid-late 20s)
Lauren is socially intelligent and emotionally open. She arrives wanting to do the right thing, to help and to fit in. As the meal goes on, she begins to understand that the politeness in this family is not neutral, it‚Äôs the core of the problem.
She is the only person not fully accustomed to this dynamic. She sees through it all, but is unable to change anything.

STEVEN (40s‚Äìearly 50s)

Steven is a typical dad. He loves his wife and understands her pain, but he has long ago decided that stepping in only makes things worse. H.e tries to keep the peace, and to keep things light-hearted. As a father he is warm and genuinely caring. He believes the family still works because he keeps things light. In his own way, he allows things to continue as they are.

ALEX (mid‚Äìlate 20s)

Alex has grown up inside a dysfunctional family and learned how to survive it. He uses humour to cut through tense moments. He wants everyone to be okay, but has never seriously imagined that things could be different.
He loves his partner Lauren and is proud to bring her home, but he is unprepared for what it means to let someone truly see his family.

Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event

 

****Only 2 weeks to go****

 

Remember: networking is an essential component of building your career!

Don't miss this opportunity to engage in inspiring conversations with a diverse array of industry professionals‚Äîbrilliant actors, visionary directors, influential producers, and skilled crew members.

 

***Why Attend?***

This event offers a welcoming environment for building meaningful industry connections that can lead to:

* Auditions and casting opportunities

* Short‚Äëfilm collaborations

* Paid work and crew placements

* Long‚Äëterm creative partnerships

 

Whether you‚Äôre an actor seeking visibility, a director assembling a team, a producer sourcing talent, or a crew member looking for new projects, you‚Äôll find valuable contacts here.

 

***Featured Guest: Lisa Barton Photography***

Lisa Barton Photography returns to showcase her work and meet attendees. If you‚Äôre considering new headshots or portfolio updates, this is an ideal chance to discuss your goals in person.

 

***Event Details***

* Date: Sunday, 22 February 2026

* Location: HOME Mcr - 2 Tony Wilson Pl, Manchester M15 4FN

* Time: 2:00 PM ‚Äì 6:30 PM

* Tickets and Further Details: Available here ‚Äì

 

[https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1925427307909](https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1925427307909)

 

Bring your enthusiasm, meet new collaborators, and expand your professional network.

Share this event with fellow actors and filmmakers who you know should be there.

Friends!

The Film Program at Cinematic Arts at CCA (formerly The Colorado Film School) invites actors of all ages to participate in our Spring 2026 Open Auditions!

Our student filmmakers are casting for a wide range of short films, narrative projects, and cinematic productions, and we are seeking performers of all backgrounds, ages, and experience levels to help bring these stories to life on screen.

Whether you are a seasoned professional, a student, or someone who simply loves acting, you are warmly invited to audition and collaborate with the next generation of filmmakers.

üìÖ Audition Dates & Times

Friday, February 6, 2026

üïô 10:00 a.m. ‚Äì 5:00 p.m.

Saturday, February 7, 2026

üïô 10:00 a.m. ‚Äì 4:00 p.m.

 

üìç Location

Lowry Studios ‚Äì Community College of Aurora

9075 E. Lowry Blvd.

Denver, CO 80230

 

üé≠ What to Prepare

Please bring a 2‚Äì3 minute prepared monologue for your primary audition.

In addition to the main audition, we will also host Satellite Auditions for specific student film productions:

‚Ä¢ These will take place in rooms throughout the building

‚Ä¢ Auditions are first-come, first-served

‚Ä¢ Actors can sign up to cold read for individual projects

‚Ä¢ We anticipate up to 10 productions casting during this event

‚Ä¢ A list of roles and productions will be available on the day of the audition

‚Ä¢ Participation in satellite auditions is optional, but highly encouraged

 

üìù How to Sign Up

Actors can sign up using the QR code on the flyer or by visiting:

Accessible Web Link:

https://www.ccaurora.edu/open-auditions

(For visually impaired users or anyone unable to scan the QR code, this link provides full access to the sign-up form.)

If you can't find a reserved space that works for you, come anyway during your preferred time. We will work you into the schedule!

We can't wait to see you this Friday or Saturday!

 

üì© Questions?

Please contact:

galina.boulgakova@ccaurora.edu

 üé• Help our students tell their stories through the magic of cinema.

topComments.text: I‚Äôm at 11:30am on Saturday. Highly recommend attending this. I‚Äôve done 5 student films.

I‚Äôm sorry but this should be posted a minimum of two weeks in advance so that we can plan and prepare for this. Posting this a day before when most of us have either booked ourselves on other agreements or just unavailable due to some other reason does not help either party involved.

items.text:
Hello all, we are looking for actors for a CU Denver student film shooting this march 

Title: The Scare

Genre: Drama, Period 

Synopsis: Terry is a normal kid having a normal childhood, with two small exceptions: her father is an American spy living in West Berlin at the height of the Cold War, and she is gradually going deaf in both ears. Every day she goes to school, does her homework, plays with dolls, and every night her family plays a game of "Scare," which unbeknownst to her, is preparation for an impending Russian invasion

Roles - 

Terry Galloway (10-12): A young girl trying to live a normal life in Berlin during the Cold War. She's also going deaf in both ears. Terry is feisty but afraid of the immense changes undertaking her life.

Trudy Galloway (14-15): Terry's older sister, anxious and too aware for her own good. 

Tenley Galloway (7-8): Terry's little sister, naive and oblivious. 

Paul (30-40): Terry's father, and a spy for the American military during the Cold War. Kind, good natured, and a natural liar.

Edna (25-40): Terry's mother. Anxious about the fate of her children. 

Edith (25-40): The family's maid. (German accent required)

Note: additional smaller roles needed, not listed 

Director, Writer: Sophii Sherman 

Based on: Mean Little Deaf Queer, Written by Terry Galloway

Producers: Dominic Spacone, Christine Galvez

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: Sophiisherman@gmail.com

Run Time: Short (~10 mins)

Compensation: Unpaid

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: Auditions are all online and will be reviewed and casted this February 

Shooting Schedule: ~mar 12-22 - 4 day shooting schedule will fall sometime within that time span depending on actor availability

Filming Location: Denver

If you are interested scan the QR code or email and reach out!

Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 6/2026

D√úSTERE ZWISCHENWELTEN, DER GEHEIMTIPP AUS S√úDKOREA UND AUSGRABUNGEN IN ST P√ñLTEN 

Die Gamingwelt war skeptisch als vor einigen Jahren ein Konsolenspiel zum Gruselhit in den Kinos avancierte. Doch aktuell schickt sich eine weitere Fortsetzung mit RETURN TO SILENT HILL an, erneut das Schaudern auf die Kinoleinwand zu bringen.

Seit dem Oscargewinner Parasite hat das koreanische Kino Hochkonjunktur. Mit dem Streifen NO OTHER CHOICE gelangt ein weiterer Film in die Kinos, dem sogar Oscarchancen einger√§umt werden. Ob der Film h√§lt was er verspricht erz√§hlt Ihnen unsere Filminsiderin Sarah Fuchs.

Clasien Swierstrak organisiert das EU XXL WANDERKINO in Wolkersdorf. Wir konnten mit der Lady, deren Wurzeln aus Holland sind, ein paar Worte wechseln. √úber historische Ausgrabungen in St P√∂lten erz√§hlt die Doku NEKROPOLIS. Wir konnten mit dem Regisseur,  Alexander Mitterecker dazu ein Interview f√ºhren. 

Abgerundet wird die Sendung wie immer mit Musik aus den Soundtracks der letzten 85 Jahre.

Mittwoch 4.2.2026 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

items.text:
CASTING CALL 
Lost Boy of the Cross is a short dramatic film (approx. 20 minutes) based on true events, exploring the childhood and early adolescence of Ray, a boy raised within Australia‚Äôs institutional care system and later abandoned to the streets of Sydney. The film follows Ray from early adolescence into his teenage years, revealing how abuse, neglect, faith, and enforced silence shaped his life long before he had the power to choose his own path.

This story is based on the life of Ray Leary, as documented in A Beautiful Boy by Kate Shayler.

We are casting an actor to portray Ray at age 14‚Äì15. This is a central, emotionally grounded role requiring strong screen presence and restraint. Ray is observant, guarded, and resilient

carrying trauma beneath the surface rather than expressing it outwardly.

Role details:

Male actor

Blonde hair, blue eyes

Actor must be 18+, but convincingly appear 14‚Äì15 years old

Naturalistic performance style essential

Non tied role (does not restrict future or concurrent work)

Acting experience welcomed but not mandatory

The story uses King's Cross as a narrative backbone not as legend or spectacle, but as the place where children failed by institutions were left to survive on their own.

Lost Boy of the Cross is intended for Australian and international film festivals, alongside selected industry, educational, and advocacy screenings. This is a trauma informed production led by an experienced director, with care, safety, and respect at the centre of the process. Full credit provided.

Email show real to albionlaneproductions@gmail.com

Hello all! My name is Abigail Rees and this is the casting call for UNCSA/Konrad Wolf Exchange short Film "Sensitivity" shooting March 28th to the 29th in Winston-Salem. It is non-union and unpaid.

If interested please reach out to **sensitivityfilm@gmail.com**

The self-tape Deadline is February 21st

Thank you for your time!

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì JENNY & POPPY (Newcastle)** 

We are currently casting **two key female roles** for a Newcastle-based short film / pilot being produced as part of a university project.

**Roles:**

**JENNY (mid - late 20s)**
Confident, sharp, and socially switched-on. Jenny is witty, emotionally intelligent, and often the voice of reason within the group. Strong presence on screen.

**POPPY (mid - late 20s)**
Warm, expressive, and empathetic. Poppy is thoughtful and emotionally open, with a grounded and natural energy. A character with depth and subtlety.

 **Location:** Newcastle (Bar No.28 & The Last Resort)
 **Shoot dates:** First two weeks of February (starting 4th Feb) ‚Äì approx. **6 days availability required**
 **Unpaid student production** (travel support available)
 Great **showreel material + headshots provided**

Submission ends 1st February.

If interested, please get in touch:

 willm.patton@gmail.com
 07495 605757

Feel free to share with anyone who may be suitable.

Thank you!

items.text:
üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì STUDENT FILM
The Man Who Came Back From the Future

Hi! My name is Yuri Kakuya, and I‚Äôm currently a student in the Foundation Program at Vancouver Film School.

We are looking for 3 roles for our final project.

‚∏ª

üé≠ ROLES

JACK (Male, preferably in his 30s‚Äì40s)

A character who exists simultaneously as the screenwriter of the film, its director, and the patient who watches it.

JESSICA (Female, preferably in her 20s)

A character who exists as a figure within Jack‚Äôs film, the actress portraying that figure, and Jack‚Äôs attending physician.

THE MAN (Male, preferably in his 20s)

A character who exists as a man who has returned from the future, the actor portraying him, and Jack‚Äôs attending physician.

‚∏ª

üìñ STORYLINE

A filmmaker documents a theory about time through a man who has already seen himself commit a murder in the future.

As past, present, and future overlap across film sets, performances, and memories, the man realizes that knowing the future may be the very thing that erases his freedom‚Äîturning choice into inevitability, and life into a film whose ending is already written.

This project is built on the concepts of metacognition and fractal structure, functioning as a cinematic apparatus that allows the audience to re-experience a central question:

Can a future that is already perceived still be called the future?

Through allegory and symbolic dialogue, the characters guide the viewer into this experiential inquiry.

‚∏ª

üì© SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS

Please submit your video audition to:

üìß recognizedtime@gmail.com

In your email, please indicate which role you are interested in.

‚∏ª

‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT NOTES

 ‚Ä¢ This is a student film, non-union, and unpaid (volunteer).

 ‚Ä¢ All cast members will receive screen credit.

 ‚Ä¢ Final rehearsals will begin one week before the first day of shooting.

 ‚Ä¢ This project is planned to be registered on IMDb.

 ‚Ä¢ Meals provided on set.

‚∏ª

üìÖ KEY DATES

 ‚Ä¢ Audition Deadline: February 15, 2026

 ‚Ä¢ Callbacks: Vancouver Film School February 21, 2026

 ‚Ä¢ Shooting Day: March 7 and 8, 2026

‚∏ª

üé• PRODUCTION INFO

 ‚Ä¢ UNION: Student Film / Non-union / Unpaid

 ‚Ä¢ FORMAT: 2160/24p, 4K (Sony FX3)

 ‚Ä¢ SHOOTING LOCATION: Vancouver, BC

 ‚Ä¢ SCRIPT AVAILABILITY: Via email

If you‚Äôre interested in this project, feel free to email me!

I‚Äôm happy to share the full screenplay with you.

Best,

Yuri Kakuya

üìß recognizedtime@gmail.com

sharedPost.text:
---

üåÄüé¨üé•üåö Exclusive Acting Workshop ‚Äì Final Version .version A.

VERY LOW COST: One-on-One Online via Skype

"This course integrates the poetic realism of Tarkovsky, the practical wisdom of Michael Caine, and the transformative techniques of Stanislavski and Method Acting. Designed to deepen your craft, it focuses on authentic emotional connection and powerful storytelling."

üé¨ Created by a British Cinematographer/Director with 31 Years of Experience and 32 Features to His Name

üåê International Experience: Having worked on films worldwide, collaborating with actors and directors, I bring real-world insights from both sides of the camera. This course is designed to give actors a deep understanding of their craft, emphasizing emotional depth and character development.

üåê IMDb: www.imdb.com/name/nm1806508

üåê Showreel: https://enkiproductions1.8b.io

---

ü§î What You Will Learn:

üåÄ Emotional Range: Master the ability to express a full spectrum of emotions, making your performances more believable and compelling.

üåÄ Character Development: Create rich, multidimensional characters by exploring their internal world, external actions, and backstory.

üåÄ Method Acting: Use personal experiences and emotions to deliver raw, authentic performances.

üåÄ Working with Directors and Crew: Learn how to hit marks, understand shooting ratios, and collaborate with crew members to enhance your performance.

üåÄ Scene Preparation: Techniques for script interpretation, emotional connection, and performing under pressure.

üåÄ Industry Standards: How to create a professional showreel and work effectively with casting directors and filmmakers.

---

üé¨ Day 1: Moment-to-Moment Acting (Stanislavski‚Äôs Approach)

üîπ Breaking a Scene Down: The use of internal visualization and meditation to "become" the character.

Character Exercise: The Hitman‚Äôs First Kill

üìç Scene: A low-rent hotel room in Manhattan, lit by a dull winter‚Äôs midday light. The sad hum of a ceiling fan, distant sirens, muted traffic below. On the bed‚Äîa brand-new sniper rifle.

üîπ Exercise 1 (Singular Emotion): Enter the room, pick up the gun, examine it, and prepare for the target. Remain fully in character.

üîπ Exercise 2 (Multiple Emotional Shifts):

1. Enter slightly out of breath, feeling relief‚Äî"I made it here. No one saw me."

2. The weight of reality sets in‚Äî"Am I really about to kill someone?"

3. Mesmerized by the artistry of the gun‚Äîdraw on memories of seeing/touching weapons.

4. Snapped back to reality by a siren‚Äîtrace the feeling of waking from a dream.

5. Decision made‚Äîmove to the window, set up the gun, and wait.

üîπ Discussion: How do actors like Heath Ledger, Daniel Day-Lewis, and Dustin Hoffman make their characters so real? Insights from my own experiences on set with actors who never broke character‚Äîeven during dinner.

Exercise 3 (If Time Allows): The Phone Call

üìç Scene: You‚Äôve done something terrible‚Äîenough to make the person you love most leave forever. You must convince them to stay.

üé≠ Goal: Improvise, using pure emotional truth, until the performance is undeniably real.

---

üé¨ Day 2: Making Your Character Believable

üîπ Understanding the Psyche: Whether playing a killer or an ordinary person, you must know your character‚Äôs mind.

Character Exercise: The Breaking Point

üìç Scene: A crowded supermarket. A tired voice announces deals over the PA. You feel unseen, unheard, frustrated‚Äîuntil suddenly, you‚Äôre holding an AK-47. (Note: These scenes are purely acting exercises. They can be altered if a student is uncomfortable.)

üîπ Alternative Scene: A character about to detonate a bomb, written in the style of Heath Ledger‚Äôs Joker.

üîπ Alternative Scene: A video call to the person you love most‚Äîtelling them why. (Scripted or improv.)

üìç Final Monologue Exercise: "Hi everyone‚Ä¶ Tomorrow‚Äôs going to be different." The last words before an irreversible decision.

üîπ Accents: Versatility in performance‚Äîworking with British, American (Deep South), and Northern Irish accents.

üîπ Final Exercise: The Power of Stillness‚Äîsit before the camera, smiling, at total peace. Convey pure serenity.

---

üé¨ Day 3: Working with a Director and Crew

üîπ Understanding Your Role: How an actor fits into the filmmaking process.

üîπ Hitting Marks & Lighting: The technical side of making performances shine.

üîπ Shooting Ratios: How they affect your performance.

üîπ Crew Collaboration: Understanding continuity, sound, makeup, cinematography, and direction.

Final Showreel Scenes (Day 3):

üé≠ Sinister: "So you really think you got away with it? You really think that?" (Improv)

üé≠ Heartbroken: "But I didn‚Äôt mean it... please, please, don‚Äôt leave me‚Ä¶" (Improv)

üé≠ Insane (Joker-like): "Mmm... if E = mc¬≤, then time versus chaos... who cares?" (Improv)

üé≠ Flat & Emotionless: "We‚Äôre born, we live, we die. That‚Äôs it." (Improv)

üîπ Goal: Draw from personal experiences and trace memories to make the performances deeply real.

---

üé¨ Day 4: Fear and Survival ‚Äì Personal Experience & Character Creation

üîπ Deep Dive: Exploring fear, survival, and desperation in character work.

Exercise 1: The Jungle Escape

üìç Scene: You‚Äôre lost in the jungle at night, exhausted, your breath the only sound. Every step is agony, but stopping means death. You call out‚Äîpleading for help. No answer.

üé≠ Emotions to Explore:

1. Fear of death ‚Äì the realization that no one is coming.

2. Desperation ‚Äì the raw instinct to survive.

3. Physical exhaustion ‚Äì feeling your body give in.

üé≠ Method Process:

1. Internal Visualization ‚Äì Close your eyes, hear the insects, the rustling leaves, your pounding heartbeat.

2. Personal Connection ‚Äì Recall a moment when you felt completely lost or afraid.

3. Scene Execution ‚Äì Let the emotions guide your body and voice.

Exercise 2: The Phone Call Redux

üìç Scene: You‚Äôre on the phone with a loved one. You need their help. If they refuse, it‚Äôs over. What do you say? What do you leave out?

üé≠ Objective: Make the desperation feel real. This is life or death.

---

Final Performance (Day 4):

Students will perform a final emotional scene, bringing together everything they‚Äôve learned. These performances will be recorded as raw material for their showreel.

---

üé¨üé• Ready to Elevate Your Acting?

This isn‚Äôt just a class‚Äîit‚Äôs an intense, immersive experience that will change the way you act forever.

üåê To Enroll: p.m.me or e.mail:

mikeenkiproductions1@gmail.com

Let‚Äôs create something unforgettable.

items.text:
Casting Call!
Non-Union, Unpaid

Longline: An Italian-Canadian family try to have a peaceful dinner in their basement while their house is under renovation which leads to a chaotic and bloody solution.

Characters:

Tony DiLeo (Caucasian): Ages 45-50. An old school Italian dad with a mobster personality and dark sense of humour.

Patty DiLeo (Caucasian): Ages 45-50. Tony‚Äôs wife who is very judgmental and likes to run her mouth a lot. 

Marco DiLeo (Caucasian): Ages 25-27. Tony and Patty‚Äôs eldest son who is a complete troublemaker and thinks he‚Äôs smarter than everyone.

Vanessa DiLeo (Caucasian): Ages 22-24. Tony and Patty‚Äôs only daughter who is a total drama queen and has the potty mouth of a truck driver.

Shooting date: Saturday, March 7th 2026

Location: Toronto, Ontario, Canada 

Actors/Actresses, send headshots and demo reels to wopsshortfilm@gmail.com by Wednesday, February 18th.

Food and drinks with be provided on set.
